Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%grams}.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim and discard the root and dark green leafy part from the @Leek{1}. Halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

When boiling, add the rigatoni to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, melt the @Butter{20%grams} with a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%grams} and sliced leek and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until the bacon is golden, ~{4-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Next, stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{125%milliliters}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @Lemon{1} into wedges. Pick the @Tarragon{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks).

In a small #bowl{}, combine the lemon zest and half the tarragon. Set your gremolata aside.

Once the sauce has reduced, stir the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams} and @Peas{120%grams} into the leek pan. Simmer until the sauce is thickened and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the cooked pasta and toss to combine.

Remove the pan from the heat, stir through the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%grams} and remaining tarragon.

Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a squeeze of lemon from a lemon wedge. Add a splash more water if needed.

Share the pasta primavera between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the tarragon gremolata to finish. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!